{
  "texts": [
    "Travelling and population moves have already resulted in an increasing number of countries which are no longer monocultural.",
    "In multicultural societies and multicultural companies bias (whether conscious or unconscious) can lead to misunderstandings and friction.",
    "Managing and alleviating friction facilitates teamwork and engenders trust which in turn helps the requirements elicitation process.",
    "In order to use positive action (identified as a prevention and mitigation strategy in this paper) for assembling a culturally diverse project team further work will be conducted, to identify concrete measures an employer/project manager(s) can take that would be permissible under discrimination legislation.",
    "The richness of multiculturalism integrates multiple views of any situation which enhances the chances of finding innovative solutions to conflicts, thus maximizing the likelihood of success."
  ]
}